The course provides a definition of innovation and its categories. It takes a systemic approach to innovations. Innovation systems are introduced on several different levels. Attention is drawn to industry-level and regional-level innovation systems. The course compares Estonian innovation policy with those of other countries. The experiences of EU, Finland and Ireland in creation of innovation policies and systems will be investigated in greater detail. The second part of the course provides an understanding about innovation management in a company. It discusses the principles of innovation strategy formation, the processes of product and service innovations, and the impact of organizational structures on the success of innovation processes.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The general objective of the course is:  a)to form understanding about the multilevel character of the innovation as a process;  b)to provide a vision of relationships between national innovation policy and innovation processes of companies; c)to give knowledge about innovation management on different (national, industry and company) levels of economy; d)to create via discussions experiences for interpretation and transfer of earlier innovation practices.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  a) knowledge of main notion concerning innovation management; b) comprehension of innovation management mechanisms on national, industry and company levels; c) knowledge about innovation systems and -policies in Estonia and in other EU member-states; d) ability to evaluate the importance of innovation management in a company and for the country's development in general; e) capability to analyze company's innovation process and to implement measures for its governance; f) capability to evaluate the efficiency of Estonian innovation system and innovation policy; g) competence to use the acquired knowledge and skills in the analysis and management of innovation processes. h) capability to recognize relationships between the national innovation policy and the possibilities for the management of innovation processes in a company.
